\par }{\ul 
\par New Cellphone Regulation
\par }\pard\plain \widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\ul 
\par }{\fs22 In the light of several queries presented to the Computer Lab Operations by so-called \ldblquote concerned students\rdblquote  on the use of cellphones inside the Computer Labs, it was agreed upon that a revised policy be implemented. 
\par 
\par Below is the revised policy on the use of cellphones:
\par 
\par 1) Cellphones should be set to silent mode upon entering the lab.
\par 2) No cellphone on top of tables. It is better to keep them inside your pockets or keep the units  
\par     under the table. Doing so will also minimize theft of the said units.
\par 3) Voice calls will be done outside. All incoming or outgoing voice calls should be entertained  
\par     outside the Computer Lab Rooms to avoid disturbing the other users.
\par 
\par *However, t}{\fs22 he following only applies during freeslot period. It is understood that if the lab is used as a classroom or when there are classes going on, similar to non-computer classrooms, it is }{\b\fs22 mandatory }{\fs22 
to turn-off all cellphones. 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs22 
\par Sanctions:}{\fs22 
\par Pursuant to Section 13.3.2.2 and Section 13.3.2.14 of the Student Handbook, any offense or violation of the above mentioned items will be awarded a Minor Offense. 
\par 
\par Likewise, any succeeding offense of the same nature will be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of the Student Handbook
\par 
\par }}